<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-08T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-08T19:00:00-05:00" n="20" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d20">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">710 Consultation (3)A/746b:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-08T20:00:00-04:00">June 8,
                                    1944—8 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>330. For Sanders from Knapp. Press statement issued by Department June
                                6<note n="53" xml:id="d20fn53">Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, June 10, 1944, p. 536.</note>, the date agreed
                            upon for Ecuadoran recognition<note n="54" xml:id="d20fn54">For
                                correspondence on the recognition of the new Government in Ecuador
                                by the United States, see <ref target="#pg_1036">pp. 1036</ref>
                                ff.</note> by most republics, stated that our decision followed
                            after consultations <pb facs="0030" n="16" xml:id="pg_16"/> among the
                            republics concerned, in compliance with Resolution XXII, and that we
                            were informing the Committee of our decision. Please so advise Dr.
                            Guani. You may also inform him that we authorized suggestions to the
                            other countries that they notify the Committee of their action, which
                            some have already indicated they propose to do. [Knapp.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>